line_1: GOOD madam, when ladies are willing,
line_2: For me I wou'd not give a shilling

line_1: I'd send it with an Heart most willing,
line_2: Tho' it shou'd cost me half a Shilling:

line_1: Who, if some Block-head should be willing
line_2: To lend him on his Soul a Shilling,

line_1: Shall I, when the kind turtle's willing,
line_2: Forego the dear delight of billing?
